<item>
            <title>[LU-12083] Interop: conf-sanity test 100 fails with &apos;lshowmount have no output MGS&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12083</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;conf-sanity test_100 fails in interop testing with &apos;lshowmount have no output MGS&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at a recent failure, 2.10.7 RC1 clients and 2.7.x servers, at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/bf2c7fb0-4306-11e9-92fe-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/bf2c7fb0-4306-11e9-92fe-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;, we see the following in the client test_log&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;setup single mount lustre success
CMD: trevis-54vm12 lshowmount -v
trevis-54vm12: sh: lshowmount: command not found
 conf-sanity test_100: @@@@@@ FAIL: lshowmount have no output MGS 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8599&quot; title=&quot;Restore lshowmount utility&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8599&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8599&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/17593/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/17593/&lt;/a&gt;, we see that conf-sanity test 100 was added to Lustre version 2.8.59. Thus, it&#8217;s clear that we need to add a Lustre version check for this test and not run this test for all interop testing with servers with version less than 2.8.59.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
